name: Sazzat Sohel
review_text: Dassam Falls is truly a hidden gem, offering a stunning escape into nature. The cascading waterfalls are mesmerizing, surrounded by lush greenery and rocky landscapes that make for a perfect, serene environment. The sound of the water crashing down is soothing, and the fresh air adds to the peaceful atmosphere. The trek to the falls is enjoyable, with well-maintained paths that make it accessible for most visitors. Its an ideal spot for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts. Definitely worth the visit for anyone looking to connect with nature and unwind!

name: Vivek Kumar
review_text:
Dasham Falls is a must-visit destination for anyone traveling near Ranchi. Its raw, untouched beauty and serene environment make it a memorable experience for families, couples, and solo travelers. Dont forget to carry your camera to capture the mesmerizing landscapes!

name: Manish Gayan
review_text:
Prepare to be awestruck by the breathtaking beauty of the falls in all their glory! With water cascading powerfully, this natural wonder is a sight to behold. After parking, get ready for a thrilling descent down a flight of stairs that leads you right to the stunning viewpoints. For those who crave an even closer encounter, make your way down to the base for an exhilarating up-close experience!

And don't worry about getting hungry while you take in the scenery--plenty of vibrant food stalls are available to satisfy your cravings and refresh your spirit. Get ready for an unforgettable adventure!

name: Santanu Bahali
review_text:
Dassam Falls is a well-known waterfall in Ranchi, Jharkhand, located about 40 km (a one-hour drive) from the city. It is the only waterfall I have visited in Ranchi, so I cant compare it to others, but I feel this place is somewhat overrated. While the waterfall is undeniably beautiful, it is not safe for bathing directly under the falls. Visitors can bathe in a designated area on one side of the falls, but personally, I did not find it very appealing.

Other Informations:-
Car Parking:- Available. But on the weekend this may not be sufficient.
Changing Room:- Not Available.
Entry Fee:- Nil

name: Anoop Pai
review_text:
Located approximately 40 kilometers from Ranchi, Dassam Falls offersa refreshing escape into nature. The well-maintained surroundings create a peaceful ambiance that is perfect for a leisurely day out. The highlight, however, is the majestic waterfall itself. As the evening approaches, the falls truly come to life, casting a mesmerizing glow and creating a breathtaking spectacle. Whether youre seeking a quiet picnic spot or a thrilling adventure, Dassam Falls has something to offer. The surrounding areas are ideal for exploring, and the waterfall provides a stunning backdrop. For those seeking a quick bite, the area boasts a variety of shops offering delicious snacks to satisfy your cravings.

name: Pankaj Kumar Mehta
review_text:
Dassam Falls is a stunning waterfall located near Taimara in the Ranchi district of Jharkhand, India. Here are some key details about Dassam Falls:

1. Height and Formation: Dassam Falls has a height of approximately 44 meters (about 144 feet) and is formed by the Kanchi River as it cascades down rocky cliffs. The waterfall is known for its picturesque and serene surroundings.

2. Natural Beauty: The falls are surrounded by lush green forests, rocky terrain, and hills, making it a popular spot for nature lovers and tourists. The scenic beauty, especially during the monsoon season when the water flow increases, attracts many visitors.

3. Accessibility: Dassam Falls is located about 40 kilometers from Ranchi, making it easily accessible for day trips. The area is well-connected by roads, and visitors can reach the falls via private vehicles or local transportation.

4. Tourist Attraction: The falls are a popular tourist destination in Jharkhand, drawing both locals and tourists. Many people visit for picnics, photography, and to enjoy the tranquil environment.

5. Adventure Activities: The area around Dassam Falls offers opportunities for adventure activities like trekking, rock climbing, and exploring the nearby forests, making it an exciting destination for adventure enthusiasts.

6. Picnic Spot: The serene environment and natural beauty make Dassam Falls an ideal picnic spot for families and groups. Many people visit the falls to relax and enjoy the sound of cascading water.

7. Flora and Fauna: The surrounding area is rich in biodiversity, with various species of plants and animals. Birdwatchers and wildlife enthusiasts often visit to observe the local wildlife.

8. Cultural Significance: Dassam Falls holds cultural importance for the local communities, and the natural beauty of the area is often celebrated in local folklore and traditions.

Dassam Falls is a captivating natural wonder that offers a perfect escape into nature, making it a must-visit destination for those exploring the Ranchi region and its surroundings.

The waterfall is situated on the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River.

name: Kewaal Chaddha
review_text:
Located near Ranchi in Jharkhand, India, is a striking natural attraction that captivates visitors with its scenic beauty. The waterfall, plunging from a height of about 44 meters, offers a dramatic view as it cascades over rugged rocks into a clear pool below. The surrounding lush greenery adds to the picturesque setting.

The area around Dassam Falls is relatively accessible, making it a popular spot for day trips. Visitors can enjoy the refreshing spray of the falls and the serene environment, ideal for photography and relaxation. However, caution is advised near the water, as the rocks can be slippery. Facilities are basic, so its wise to bring your own refreshments and essentials.

Overall, Dassam Falls is a beautiful and easily reachable destination for those looking to enjoy a natural escape and experience the splendor of Indias waterfalls.

name: Dalbir Singh
review_text:
Beautiful, close to highway, easily accessible, must visit.
Lets me share the history as from internet source: Dasham Falls, a natural wonder, holds cultural significance as well. The name "Dasham" or "Dassam" derives from the local Mundari language, signifying "ten." According to legend, ten brothers faced divine retribution after killing a sacred deer belonging to the goddess Durga. She transformed them into ten streams that cascade down a cliff, resulting in the waterfall known as Dasham Falls. Locally, it is also referred to as Durga Falls or Daesal Falls, honoring the goddess.

For centuries, Dasham Falls has been integral to the traditions and history of tribal communities residing nearby--the Munda, Oraon, Ho, and Santhal tribes. During festivals like Holi, Diwali, Chhath Puja, and Sarhul, they perform rituals and offer prayers at this sacred site. Additionally, Dasham Falls symbolizes freedom and resistance, as it was a location where tribal leaders fought against British colonial rule in the 19th century. 
Some internet source alos claim fossils and limestone in this area which I doubt.
Enjoy the Place ,take less pictures and relax just feel the falls,let the falls wash away your sins.

Weekend

review_text:
Somehow waterfalls in Jharkhand are so underrated.

Dadsam is one of them. Is has also been the most dangerous waterfall around ranchi. One has to be careful during rainy season.
There isn't trekking trail or climbing to reach to waterfall. A few steps down and you are at the main waterfall unlike other waterfalls in the area.

Definitely a mist visit in monsoon. Not much to see during summers. This video is captured in July. It will become more dense after few more showers.

name: Digvijay Kumar Yadav
review_text:
Located near the Taimara village in the Ranchi district, Dasham Falls, also known as Dassam Falls, is a spectacular waterfall in the state of Jharkhand which is a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. Cascading down a height of 144 ft., the waterfall boast of utter serenity, peace and calm. The area surrounding the spot is engulfed in rich greenery, that makes it an ideal picnic place in the region. To reach the spot, you will have to climb a flight of stairs. You can also stop in between and stare at the gorgeous scenery surrounding it.The waterfall is basically a Nick Point, also known as Knick Point, which means that it has been developed over the years due to the break in the rocky slopes in a longitudinal manner. For the same reason, it is not ideal to swim or to step into the water as the current is strong and the ground is uneven. Other than that, the region echoes with the gurgling sound of water which is like music to the ears, and is perfect to relax and rejuvenate.The word Dasham or Dassam is a derivative of the mundari language word 'Da: song' which means the process of pouring water. 'Da:' means water and 'song' meaning 'pouring'. Formerly, the name Da: song, however, over the years, it came to be called Dasham or Dassam.

name: Papiya Saha
review_text:
A natural spellbound waterfall. A must visit place. We visited in March 2024. It was a Holi time. It looks even more beautiful if you go at the end of Summer or Rainy season. I loved the manageable stairs. If anyone has a problem going to the ground level, they also can enjoy the full scenic beauty of the waterfall by sitting the chairs at any view point. You can also enjoy the Chana masala. You can buy gift items. No entry fee. But parking is available. You have to pay. We relaxed and enjoyed the beauty. While returning, we had our lunch at a nearby reasonable restaurant, Hotel Panchwati. AC and non AC both available. Have a nice and safe journey. Avoid any unnecessary incident near waterfalls.

name: Arindam Mitra
review_text:
The Dassam Falls is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. The water falls from a height of 44 metres (144 ft). The sound of water echoes all around the place. Dassam Falls at one of the edges of the Ranchi plateau is one of the many scarp falls in the region.

The Dassam Falls is an example of a nick point caused by rejuvenation. Knick point, also called a nick point or simply nick, represents breaks in slopes in the longitudinal profile of a river caused by rejuvenation. The break in channel gradient allows water to fall vertically giving rise to a waterfall.

The water of the Dassam Falls is very clean and clear. It is natural for a tourist to be enticed to enter the water for a bath or swim but tourists are warned not to do so because of the current that is generated. There have been many cases of drowning in Dassam Falls. Nine people died of drowning between 2001 and 2006.

Weekday

name: Shashi _
review_text:
Loved it. Scenic and relaxing place. Natural White Noise.
- Visited two spots, one right at the waterfall where it was crowded and one downstream where it was quiet.
- Paid parking
- Bottled water, Soft drinks, packaged snacks, Chana Salad, and Sugarcane juice were available.
- Didnt see a y Tea/Coffee option.
- Bath towels and wooden home decor items were also on sale.
- There is a boat, just as a prop for taking photos in. Photo prints on site.
- Navigating rocks was tricky with a helmet in one hand .
I recommend keeping your hands free and wearing trekking shoes or something that has traction on rocks.

name: Harsh Kumar Singh
review_text:
A bit of geography:
Dassam waterfall is on Kanchi river.
Johna and Sita waterfall are on Rarhu river.
Hundru is on Subarnarekha river.
Both Kanchi and Rarhu join Subarnrekha , almost together!

Good waterfall. But, a lot of crowd coming to picnic here and people have ruined the beauty of this waterfall. A lot of garbage. People camping and cooking in herds. Parking is a problem as well.
Go to Dassam on weekdays to avoid crowd.
Or go to Johna.
Rainy season has its own risks so, avoid going in rainy season.

name: Pinaki Ranjan Das
review_text:
Dassam Waterfall, Jharkhand: Natures Majestic Cascade

Nestled within the pristine landscapes of Jharkhand, Dassam Waterfall stands as a majestic spectacle, captivating all who venture to witness its awe-inspiring beauty. Located near the Taimara village in Ranchi, this natural marvel offers a breathtaking retreat, combining the raw power of cascading water with the serene allure of untouched wilderness.

Dassam Waterfall, also known as Dassam Ghagh, commands attention with its sheer grandeur. The waterfall plunges from an impressive height, creating a mesmerizing display of cascading water that reverberates through the surrounding hills. The thunderous sound adds to the immersive experience, making it a visual and auditory feast for visitors.

The journey to Dassam Waterfall is a scenic odyssey through dense forests and picturesque landscapes. As visitors approach the falls, the sound of rushing water becomes a melodic prelude, heightening the anticipation for the breathtaking reveal. The lush greenery and crisp air contribute to the overall serenity of the surroundings.

Dassam Waterfall caters to adventure enthusiasts, beckoning them to explore the rugged terrain surrounding the cascade. Trekking trails offer a thrilling journey through the wilderness, providing panoramic views of the falls from different vantage points. The adventure adds a dynamic element to the visit, attracting those seeking an adrenaline-infused experience.

Beyond its natural allure, Dassam Waterfall is steeped in local folklore and cultural significance. Legends and tales passed down through generations infuse the site with a sense of mystique. The falls hold a special place in the hearts of the local community, adding a cultural layer to the overall experience.

Dassam Waterfall is accessible from Ranchi, with well-marked roads leading to the site. Basic facilities, including parking areas, refreshment stalls, and seating spots, cater to the needs of visitors. The well-maintained pathways ensure that exploring the vicinity is both safe and enjoyable.

Dassam Waterfall emerges as a natural masterpiece, inviting travelers to witness the harmonious dance of water and earth. Whether seeking adventure, cultural enrichment, or a peaceful communion with nature, Dassam Waterfall captivates with its unspoiled beauty, leaving an indelible mark on all who venture into its enchanting realm in the heart of Jharkhand.

name: Pradeep Bhardwaj
review_text:
Dasam Falls is located 34 km from Ranchi city on Ranchi-Tata Road near Tamara village. The place is also known as Dasam Garh. The main water source of this waterfall is River Kachni, which comes here from a height of 144 feet. The unique feature of this fall is that when the waterfall is seen, 10 streams of water are also seen falling.
The approximate distance of Dasham Falls from Birsa Munda Airport is 31 kilometers.
The approximate distance of Dasham Falls from Ranchi Railway Station is 26 kilometers.
The approximate distance of Dasham Falls from Birsa Munda Bus Terminal is 24 kilometers.
Visited on
Weekend

name: Jayant Yadav
review_text:
The place is also known as Dassam Garh. The major water source of this waterfall is River Kachni, which falls here from an altitude of 144 feet. The unique feature of this fall is that when the waterfall is seen, 10 water streams are also seen falling.
The Dassam Falls is 40 kilometres (25 mi) from Ranchi on NH 33 or Ranchi-Jamshedpur highway. The Dassam Falls is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River.
About 40 kms from Ranchi, this is indeed a must visit place in Ranchi. Its off NH33 and has to get down over 300 steps to reach the landing level. The fall which is across Kanchi river is beautiful falling from an height of 144 feet.
The Dassam Falls is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. The water falls from a height of 44 metres (144 ft).

Along with the stairs there are viewing decks at regular intervals hence one can stop and enjoy the view from there.

name: Sayan Chakroborty
review_text:
The most aggressive and massive waterfalls in Jharkhand. Unlike other waterfalls there is no entry fee but only a parking fee. The place is not under JTDC but is maintained by the local Mundari people of the Taimara village. Comparatively fewer stairs than other popular waterfalls in the area. Multiple viewpoints and selfie points around the falls. One can climb the rocks and have a nice refreshing bath in the falls but it is advised to be careful while stepping on the rocks as they are very slippery and can cause fatal accidents which is why there are guards observing the falls and blowing whistles whenever they notice tourists climbing unsafe spots. Overall a very nice place to visit and a must watch tourist destination.

name: RUPASREE DEY BHOWMICK
review_text:
Just amazing.... Loved a lot...nice sitting arrangements for elder & children... But needs more personnel to avoid accidents at risky points.

Dassam Falls is a waterfall located near Taimara village in Bundu police station of Ranchi district in the Indian state of Jharkhand. It is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. The water falls from a height of 44 metres (144ft)

The name Dassam is a changed form of word Da:song which means in Mundari language the act of pouring water. The falls is also known as Dassam Ghagh.

The best time to visit the Dassam Falls is during the monsoons, from July to September, when the water is abundant and the falls is at its most spectacular. However, it is also a popular spot during the winter months, from December to February, when the weather is mild.

The falls is a popular tourist destination and is easily accessible from Ranchi. There is a parking lot at the top of the falls and a short walk leads down to the viewing area. There are also a few restaurants and stalls selling food and souvenirs near the falls.

Here are some tips for visiting Dassam Falls:

Wear comfortable shoes as there is a fair amount of walking involved.

Bring a camera to capture the beauty of the falls.

Be prepared for crowds, especially during the monsoons.

Take care not to get too close to the edge of the falls as it can be slippery.

I hope this helps.

name: Nayan Bhalotia
review_text:
Dassam Falls, located around 40kms from Ranchi and approximately 90kms from Jamshedpur, is a true gem of natures beauty in Jharkhand. I have been fortunate enough to visit this enchanting place multiple times, and it never fails to leave me in awe.

The first thing that strikes you as you approach the falls is the mesmerizing view. The waterfall is absolutely beautiful, and the force of water cascading down is simply amazing. The sight of the water gushing with such power is a sight to behold, and the sounds of the roaring water add to the overall experience.

The authorities have done a commendable job in maintaining the site for tourists. Visitors are allowed to explore and get close to the base of the falls, except during the monsoon season when access to the base is restricted for safety reasons. This restriction is understandable, considering how slippery the stones can get during that period. Its crucial to be cautious while navigating the area.

Speaking of which, I must admit that the best time to visit Dassam Falls is undoubtedly during the monsoon season. Even though getting to the base is off-limits, witnessing the sheer power of the water during this time is an unforgettable experience. The energy and intensity of the falls are at their peak, making it a breathtaking spectacle.

As for dining options, while there are a couple of local dhabas near the falls, I would advise against choosing them, especially if you are with your family. These eateries might not meet the hygiene standards you expect. Instead, I recommend Raj Darbar Dhaba or Panchvati, located approximately 20kms away from the falls, on the main highway NH33. These places offer better dining experiences with more reliable food options.

I must mention that Dassam Falls is no longer the scary, slippery place we might have heard about in our childhood. The efforts put into maintenance and safety have transformed it into a must-visit destination in Jharkhand. Whether you are a nature enthusiast, an adventure seeker, or simply looking for a serene spot to relax, Dassam Falls has something to offer for everyone.

Weekend

name: Rohit Maurya
review_text:
The Dassam Falls is a waterfall located near Taimara village in Bundu police station of Ranchi district in the Indian state of Jharkhand.

Dasham Falls is located about 40 kilometers from Ranchi on the Ranchi Jamshedpur road. The real name of Dasam Falls is Da:Som. The word Da:Som is from the local Mundari language. The word Da:Som is made up of two words Da: and Som. Da: means water and Som means accumulation.
Visited on
Public holiday

name: Satyam Shandilya
review_text:
One of the best tourist attraction near Ranchi.
Located near Bundu (In Ranchi - Jamshedpur highway)

You will be mesmerized by seeing the beauty of this place...

Stairs are available to reach to the bottom level of this fall... but be cautious when you are here...

Government has also placed many seating arrangements for the convenience of the visitors/tourists...

People visit this place for picnics...
You will also get to try local fruits and vegetables... as the local people sell their produces...

Best time to visit is during rainy seasons to see the beauty of this waterfall... or during winters...

name: Arindam Manna
review_text:
Dassam falls is a natural waterfall across the river khanchi. It is located around 40KM from Ranchi The Dassam Falls is an example of a nick point caused by rejuvenation. Knick point, also called a nick point or simply nick, represents breaks in slopes in the longitudinal profile of a river caused by rejuvenation. The break in channel gradient allows water to fall vertically giving rise to a waterfall.

name: Himadri Bhakat
review_text:
One of the good water falls in Jharkhand. It is situated around 10KM from the NH33. You have to Rs.50.00 at the entry gate maintained by local people. The local people are very good. The place is neat and clean and you can find food during weekends. There are some shops for local handicraft materials, fresh fruits and vegetables. But the water flow is very less during these days. For full waterflow you have to visit during July - August. Overall the place is very good and beautiful in raw nature. If good roads are made then it will add more value to the place.

name: Ajit Kumar
review_text:
I recently visited the Dasham Waterfall and was blown away by its natural beauty. The waterfall is located in a lush, green area that is perfect for a peaceful and refreshing hike. The trail is well-maintained and easy to navigate, making it suitable for visitors of all ages and fitness levels.

The waterfall itself is stunning, cascading down a rocky cliff with misty spray that creates a beautiful rainbow. The sound of the water falling is soothing and creates a perfect ambiance. There were plenty of spots to stop and take in the view and also to take some great pictures.

The facilities were also very clean and well-maintained, including bathrooms, picnic tables, and viewing platforms. The staff were friendly and helpful, providing information about the waterfall and the surrounding area.

Overall, I highly recommend visiting the Dasham Waterfall. It is a perfect spot for a peaceful and refreshing day out in nature. The waterfall is truly a marvel of nature and is definitely worth a visit.
Visited on
Public holiday

name: Vishal Kumar
review_text:
It is a very cool place, I went there on 1st January. There was a lot of traffic on the way, it took us about 1 hour to reach the fall from the main road, due to traffic jam. Due to it being the month of January, there was very little water in the fall, light water was coming from above. We went till the other side of the fall. There are big smooth stones at the top on which the feet slip a lot. I had more fun up there than down there. But it may be difficult to go up during the rainy season when it is full of water. But at the same time, it is more fun to see the view from above and also the waterfall. I will try to go there again in rainy days or should go only in rainy days when the water flow is at full speed.

Some of the stones are slippery and hence proper care to be taken.

Cons: to use the unmaintained and unclean toilet, one has to pay rs10/head (ironically the entry fee was rs10 also). And i thought we are spending crores of our tax payers money for swatch bharat.

review_text:
Dassam Falls is about 35kms away from Ranchi and on Ranchi Tata Highway.
Connectivity is excellent and you can take a 4 wheeler or even a 2 wheeler if u wish to.
Falls is really nice with water flowing from 144 feet and the best part is you dont need to take too lany steps to reach the bottom area unlike Jonha falls.
We went on 31st Dec 2022 and Cooking food was not allowed near the waterfall but was very much allowed at the top of the waterfall.

Mobile connectivity for Vodafone was horribly bad showing no signal for most of the time.

name: Ravi Kant
review_text:
Nice experience.. picturesque location.. but remain crowded especially in weekends during winter.

Family planning for picnic should reach there early to secure a nice place and parking , else gets very crowded after 10:00 AM. Charges of drinking water there is quite high , reaches 50-75 for a jar of water. Toilet is not well maintained owing to the huge crowd.

There is another fall downstream .. which is not so crowded. One can also take bath in the stream just before the Dassam Falls , looks like a giant swimming pool.

Watch your footsteps while skipping stones , some are quite slippery and this place was notorious for quick sands but presence of guard and off season other than monsoon makes it safe.

Parking charges is daylight Robbery. It is around 10 kms form the TATA RANCHI Highway.. coming from bundu ( TATA) side it is just after Taimara ghati temple.

Very good place to visit to visit for picnic. The beauty is very mesmerising. You can enjoy the top view as well as bottom view. There are stairs available to go downhill. The guards are also there looking for the safety. Down the hill there are various points where you can sit and enjoy the beauty. You can cook , bring or dine in the food. At down no plastic are allowed. Parking charges are different for different vehicles. For car it is 50 and mini bus 200

name: Hitendra Chauhan
review_text:
Very beautiful waterfall. It would be good to go early in the morning. Very beautiful location for photography. Those coming to Tatanagar or Ranchi should not miss this.
Very nice and spectacular waterfall and location
Very nice facility to go down
Such waterfalls are rarely seen on a flowing river.
This must be a wonderful sight in the rain.

The best thing is that despite being so public there was no filth at all.
For this the local public and Jharkhand government deserve thanks.

name: Sambit Khuntia
review_text:
Quite a scenery to cherish & rejuvenate every time one happens to be at this place. Theres nothing wrong with the place.

The issue is with the Tourism Dept. A beautiful place as this one can easily be a hotspot tourist attraction. There arent much of a choice with any food stalls, snacks, beverages etc. No proper counter for assistance or information should any guest like to have. Theres nothing much except for the natural beauty. Govt. really needs to address this issue & this is why people arent turning up in huge nos.

name: Kalyan Bhaskar
review_text:
Enough has been written about the Dassam Falls, so would share only what we felt could come handy to future travellers:

1) It takes about 15 minutes to reach the Falls once you leave the Ranchi Tata Highway (NH 33) and take the road leading to the falls.
2) The road for some part is one lane and one has to ensure one does not overspeed. One also to remain cautious about not hurting the numerous goat/chicken on the road, especially around huts/houses. One may need go shell out upto Rs 10,000 if an animal is hurt.
3) There is decent parking space for upto 30 cars- parking fees of Rs 50. If one wants to skip paying the fee, one can park in a small field about 100 m from the parking entrance. It takes about 5 min walk to reach the Falls from that field.
4) The place is not very friendly for those with mobility issues. There are small eateries offering snacks, beverages, and food like rice, egg curry, fish, chicken, dal, pakoda, kachori, bread etc. Besides there are villagers selling guava, cucumber, and sprouts.
5) Be wary of the monkeys that loiter around the entrance to the falls. There is a toilet near the entrance. It is not the best in terms of cleanliness but is not the worst either.
6) One can enjoy the sight of the waterfalls from different locations- one from a covered seating within 10 steps of getting down from the parking area, the second after getting down further (about 20 steps), the third after further 20 steps down, and the final one after reaching the rocks near the falls. There is a small barricade (red cloth is the identifier) separating the territory marked dangerous. Visitors must not get adventurous and cross that barricade as there have been accidents in the past.
7) Getting up to the larking area from the rocks/falls can be very tiring considering the height one has to climb.
8) It was very unfortunate to see plastic bottles, lids, and packaging thrown in the water and near the rocks.
9) At the quickest, one can cover the falls in 20-30 mins and at a more relaxed pace, one can cover it in 1 hour.

Overall a very soothing and enjoyable trip.
Visited on
Weekend

name: Nitin Kumar
review_text:
DASSAM FALLS - It is located in the dense forest 40 km away from Ranchi in Jharkhand. The Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River fall from the height of 144 Ft. Few small villages set their home here and gets their livelihood mostly from the forest. Both the side has been beautification with sitting arrangements and safety walls.

In summer, very hard to see water falling but overall environment have been very calm and mesmerizing. Several species of birds chirping to welcome everyone.

The falls give its full view in the Monsoon. It becomes gorgeous then. The air has been filled with it's heavy sound. And every year it takes lives as its rule. Adventure enthusiasts are requested not to step in on the rock and take bath. This falls are not suitable for taking bath. Nobody knows when the river carries the water in full swing and drowned away.

Winter is the best season to be visited there. The water comes clean. The sky becomes clear and Several Eye-catching birds fly round the corner. Please carry sufficient water and Lunch packet. Snacks and Local foods are available. It becomes a favourite Picnic Spot during Winter.

Motorable Roads are well maintained by local authority. But no Local Transportation runs between Ranchi and Dassam Falls. Transportation should be arranged privately. Best will be arranged from the Hotel itself and registered Cab/SUV provider. They have every bit of knowledge about this place. And should be left the place before Sun Set.

name: Deep Narayan Singh
review_text:
Yes Five stars. 

Ok Im going to review this place on some parameters like :-

I experienced this beautiful and adventurous place on 24th of July 2022.
All the required or minimal facilities for tourists are available here. Separate toilets are also opened for male and female. Scenic points are also built there. Resting areas and shades are also well developed here. Minor shops are there which offers some food related stuffs. Not all places are accessible by wheelchair. So it becomes difficult to carry them with you. There is need to give an options to handicapped people as well. Guards are there for your safety. A local ticket is levied here for parking.

Im sharing some tips with you. Kindly follow these to enjoy more adventurous journey.

* [Tips] :- Carry your own food related stuffs.

One thing that you have to remember that nearby shops will charge some extra additional taxes on each and every products that they offers there. So you have to spend some more even for basic things. Avoid purchase at that place.

* [Tips] :- The stairs are very slippery in nature especially during rainy season.

Try to avoid to go more inside the waterfall area. All the stairs and rocks becomes more slippery and very dangerous for walking.

* [Tips] :- Comes early and explore more.

See there are different ways to reach this place. All paths will leads you to the same destination but with different angles and views. So, if you want to explore the whole area than I strongly recommend you to come early in the morning because there are three different points at same place with three different beautiful angles to explore and to experience.

* [Tips] :- Dont dare to swim especially if you dont know how to swim.

There are lots of cases where you found that people are dying continuously at this place because of drowning. Avoid to take bath especially during the rainy season.

* [Tips] :- Keep an eye on your childrens.

Generally people come here to enjoy but during this leisure time they ignored their children and it leads to an avoidable accident.

Follow me on Google Maps to be updated regularly.

* KNOW MORE ABOUT DASSAM FALLS :-

The Dassam Falls (also known as Dassam Ghagh) is a waterfall located near Taimara village in Bundu police station of Ranchi district in the Indian state of Jharkhand.

Elevation- 336 metres (1,102 ft)
Total height- 44 metres (144 ft)
Number of drops- 2
Watercourse- Kanchi River

Dassam is a changed form of word Da:song which means in mundari language the act of pouring water. Da: means water and song means pouring or measuring. The water fall resembles like somebody is pouring water so the name was Da:song earlier but afterwards the name was changed to Dassam.

The Dassam Falls is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. The water falls from a height of 44 metres (144 ft). The sound of water echoes all around the place. Dassam Falls at one of the edges of the Ranchi plateau is one of the many scarp falls in the region.

The Dassam Falls is an example of a nick point caused by rejuvenation. Knick point, also called a nick point or simply nick, represents breaks in slopes in the longitudinal profile of a river caused by rejuvenation. The break in channel gradient allows water to fall vertically giving rise to a waterfall.

The water of the Dassam Falls is very clean and clear. It is natural for a tourist to be enticed to enter the water for a bath or swim but tourists are warned not to do so because of the current that is generated. There have been many cases of drowning in Dassam Falls.

The Dassam Falls is 40 kilometres (25 mi) from Ranchi on NH 33 or Ranchi-Jamshedpur highway.

Keep this place as it is which means dont litter your waste and stuffs here and there. Kindly throw it in the dustbin.

name: aaron stark
review_text:
About 40 kms from Ranchi, this is indeed a must visit place in Ranchi. Its off NH33 and has to get down over 500 steps to reach the landing level. The fall which is across Kanchi river is beautiful falling from an height of 144 feet. There is car park and also small shops selling souvenirs and also some small tea shops.
Dassam Falls is so nice. One can spend hours looking at the splendid sight of water jumping from a height and forming beautiful patterns. One does not need to take a huge number of stairs up or down. I would recommend a visitor not to waste money and time for visiting Hudru or Jonha falls. At both of these places, one needs to cover more than 500 steps down and equal number of steps up, to see (at least) moving water coming from a small height.

A must visit place while in Ranchi

name: Ahsan Taqweem
review_text:
Good place
Very soothing
If you want to have peace of mind, want to just go out of your regular city life, just go to this place. The sound of flowing water, its coolness will just mesmerise you. One suggestion would be to not visit this place in summer as it has less shades where you can hide and it would be just too hot.
Visit this in the months of February to mid-March or October or November. That would be perfect time to visit.
We went to this place in March end and it was too hot tbh, the water was a bit less, but the feeling of just getting inside those small ponds itself was great.
The best part is not just the destination but also the roads with so much greenery around is amazing.
Would definitely recommend to visit once atleast.

name: king cobra entertainment
review_text:
A beautiful and calm place, where water was there even during summer, a nice place for family picnic outing, a no-plastic zone, some stalls are there to provide light refreshments. A small childrens park is also there as an added attraction. Well maintained with space for parking and hygienic facilities of Toilet exists.

On the way to the Falls from the nearby cities, the beauty of the mountains and nature on the way is a captivating sight to behold.

But entry is only till halfway down even then its worth the visit. A memorable trip to become a part of nature...Far from Maddening Crowd.

name: Gautam Chatterjee
review_text:
Dassam falls is located in Jharkhand state of India. It is located near Ranchi. You have to drive 10 km from Ranchi at Ranchi - Jamshedpur highway & then take right turn & then drive through villages & forest further 10 km to reach Dassam falls. There is a check naka where you have to pay a little money to enter Dassam arena. Local village people or boy would collect this money from you & issue panchayat receipt. The falls is a magnificent one with water jumps down from a height of 144 feet. There are few
snacks & tea counters at this place. There is parking place.

name: Bansilal Kumar
review_text:
The Dassam Fall is one of the beautiful water fall of Jharkhand. Dassam Falls is situated at 34 km from the city of Ranchi it is actually located at Ranchi-Tata road near the Taimara village. The Taimara village is 10km away from Ranchi- Tata Highway. The place is also known as Dassam Garh. The major water source of this waterfall is River Kachni, which falls here from an altitude of 144 feet. The unique feature of this fall is that when the waterfall is seen, 10 water streams are also seen falling.
The Dassam fall is surrounded by dense forest and mountain, people from different parts of India visit this place to see the natural beauty of Jharkhand.
This place is favourite picnic destination for local people of Ranchi and jamshedpur.
The Dassam fall is one of the beautiful gift of nature to Jharkhand.
This is place is favourite tourist destination of neighbour states of Jharkhand like West Bengal, Chattisgarh, Oddish etc.
To visit this place by air nearest Airport is Birsa Munda International Airport Ranchi.
By train nearest Railway station is Ranchi Junction from Airport to Dassam fall or from Ranchi Railway station to Dassam fall tourist can easily take Cabs, taxi and bus to visit this beautiful water fall.
If anyone wants to see the natural beauty or water falls of Jharkhand must visit this place you will really love this place.

name: Shubham Gupta
review_text:
A must place to visit if are around ranchi. Though it is very far from many city of ranchi. But it is worth taking the effort. The lush green forest , rising hills , waving roads and the magnificent fall will make you feel awake and connected to nature. You can even bath under the fall in one if its branches but carefully. You can have a picnic here with your family carry whatever you want to and cook and eat. Few food shops are also available. Car parking is available.
Enjoy and have fun.

P.S. Take the right road towards the right side if the fall , if you reach the opposite of the fall you will have to take a long way to the other side of the fall which is the main side or you cross from the top but its risky and you can get hurt.

name: Neel kamal Bhartia
review_text:
Dassam is one of the Highest falls of the state of Jharkhand. There is a stairs to down which takes few minutes, but to climb up, its over 100s of steps. It has water all round the year, although like every other water fall, Monsoon is the best season to watch the might of a water fall. You can go down all round the year, but in rainy days, one has to take utmost precautions.
In Dassam, lots of viewpoint from different access areas has been erected to watch fall of water but all has different route to reach. There are few eateries at the up of the fall which serves local dishes & packaged snacks. Other than monsoon, winters are the best season to visit.

name: Partha Pratim Sarkar
review_text: Just spectacular... nothing less, may be more, yes I am taking about Dassam Falls, the most majestic and serene among the Mighty Three...Hundru, Jonha and Dassam.. which are the major crowed- pullers of Ranchi. Dassam is very unique in the sense that it originated from river Kechni ( not Kanchi as most people say it ), a tributary of Subarnarekha. Not only that it has 10 waterstreams and when all of them started their actions...Oh God, its a marvel to watch. A distance of 35 km from Ranchi and a downward journey of 350 well-maintained cemented stirs, you will be there my dear. And its the most traveller- friendly among the three...less accident- prone.

review_text: Very good place, very interesting place, I visited a very nice place, Dassam falls. Very fast water was falling. name: Munna Zahwan
review_text: The Dassam falls is situated in the Ranchi district of Jharkhand and is one of India's most beautiful waterfalls. The name of this waterfall Dassam means act of pouring water which was derived from the word Da:song which is Mundari language. When you look at this waterfall, you will realize why this name was given. It does look like somebody is pouring water from the top. The sound of the water flowing in full vigor is echoed all around the place. What better than spending an evening listening to the beautiful sounds of nature with no city chaos! The water of this particular waterfall is very clean and clear. And this is one of the many reasons why so many people prefer visiting the Dassam falls. You can take a dip in the water at the base but if you visit the waterfall during heavy rains, ensure that you avoid swimming or bathing since it can get a tad dangerous. During rains the waters can generate current pulling people deep inside causing drown incidents. The waterfall here is created thanks to the Kanchi River that falls from a height of 144 feet. A one day picnic is all it needs with friends or family to make the most of Dassam falls and feel rejuvenated

name: Manish Vishwa
review_text:
LocationRanchi district, Jharkhand, IndiaCoordinates23deg08'36''N 85deg27'59''E.Elevation336 metres (1,102 ft)Total height44 metres (144 ft)Number of drops2Average widthdWatercourseKanchi River

EtymologyEdit

Dassam is a changed form of word Da:song which means in mundari language the act of pouring water. Da: means water and song means pouring or measuring. The water fall resembles like somebody is pouring water so the name was Da:song earlier but afterwards the name was changed to Dassam.

The fallsEdit



Dasam Falls

The Dassam Falls is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. The water falls from a height of 44 metres (144 ft).[2] The sound of water echoes all around the place.[3] Dassam Falls at one of the edges of the Ranchi plateau is one of the many scarp falls in the region.[4]

The Dassam Falls is an example of a nick point caused by rejuvenation. Knick point, also called a nick point or simply nick, represents breaks in slopes in the longitudinal profile of a river caused by rejuvenation. The break in channel gradient allows water to fall vertically giving rise to a waterfall.[5]

The water of the Dassam Falls is very clean and clear. It is natural for a tourist to be enticed to enter the water for a bath or swim but tourists are warned not to do so because of the current that is generated. There have been many cases of drowning in Dassam Falls.[6] Nine people died of drowning between 2001 and 2006. [7]

TransportEdit

The Dassam Falls is 40 kilometres (25 mi) from Ranchi on NH 33 or Ranchi-Jamshedpur highway.

name: DrMoujhuri Nandi
review_text: Located at Bundu valley near Ranchi this picturesque falls is a beauty to behold. Along the Ranchi Tata highway , a detour on the left and a travel of 10kms along Dassam falls road takes you to the cascade. It is located 110 kms from Jamshedpur and 30 kms from Ranchi. The falls has been created due to the waters of river Kanchi falling through a height of 144ft. The sound echoes through the surroundings and thus the name which was originally"da song" has now denigrated to "Dassam falls". The path to the bottom of the falls is through a series of well maintained steps. There are several restaurants for refreshments and well maintained washrooms at the site. Various view points constructed give you myriad views of the falls from different angles. A must visit place in Jharkhand

name: Nitesh kumar
review_text:
Dangerous yet beautiful - the word came in my mind for review the place.

Second is don't fight with the locals, pay them few 20-50 rupees of they ask for parking charge. We were 7-8 young people who indulge a a fight with locals there for not paying the parking fee (since it was not authorised & no receipt they were giving)
After all the hue & cry- finally we paid them the parking charges.

About 40 kms from Ranchi, this is indeed a must visit place in Ranchi. Its off NH33 and has to get down over 300 steps to reach the landing level. The fall which is across Kanchi river is beautiful falling from an height of 144 feet.

Dassam is a changed form of word Da:song which means in mundari language the act of pouring water. Da: means water and song means pouring or measuring. The water fall resembles like somebody is pouring water so the name was Da:song earlier but afterwards the name was changed to Dassam.

The water of the Dassam Falls is very clean and clear. It is natural for a tourist to be enticed to enter the water for a bath or swim but tourists are warned not to do so because of the current that is generated. There have been many cases of drowning in Dassam Falls.Nine people died of drowning between 2001 and 2006.

review_text:
This year falls are hungry...

One of the amazing experience of my life. Dassam Falls, the name has been derived from the number of the streams that fall from a distance of 164 feet above from the River kanchi Dassam falls is also known as Dassam Ghagh This is amongst one of the other beautiful waterfalls of the region for which tourists come from everywhere and it has greenery all around. Its musical and empowering the tunes and melody that you encounter, is a different feeling in all. It is not recommended to play and/or bath in as it is very dangerous, especially for kids It you are interested in recreational activities, there are facilities provided on the kanchi River. Is located on the Ranchi- Tata road which is approximately 34 kms from Ranchi.

name: Sudip Kumar
review_text: Dassam fall is situated at Dassam 35 km from Ranchi city. It is one of the best fall in Ranchi. Easy to go there from NH which is heading toward Jamshedpur. Best place for picnic with friends and family especially for kids, you can also make food here. This area is controlled by local tribes, and fully surrounded by thik forest. The timing is 9am to 4pm, after that the gate were closed. There is too much greenery every where. The fall is 144 ft high which make it more beautiful. You can take bath here, and also take too many selfies. There is frequent cultural fest organized by local people to entertain the tourists.

name: Parthasarathi Mukhopadhyay
review_text:
The name Dassam comes from the local Da:song which in Mundari language means, the act of pouring water. Da: means water and song means pouring or measuring. The waterfall looks like or is shaped like somebody is pouring water so the name - Dassam !!

The place - including the toilets are clean. Lots of parking place. And finally when you actually step down to the view points, the view is great. There are three view points, sensibly constructed at different levels that affords different views.

There are a number of restaurants on the plaza thats on the hill opposite the waterfall. So food and snacks wont be a problem for those driving in from Ranchi or jamshedpur.

name: Akash Kumar
review_text:
The Dassam Falls is situated at 34 km from the city of Ranchi on Ranchi-Tata road near the Taimara village. The place is also known as Dassam Garh. The major water source of this waterfall is River Kachni, which falls here from an altitude of 144 feet. The unique feature of this fall is that when the waterfall is seen, 10 water streams are also seen falling.

By Air

Nearest airport is Birsa Munda Airport which is 31 km away from this

By Train

It is almost 26 km away from Ranchi Railway Station

By Road

Birsa Munda Bus Stand kantatoli is 24 km away from dassam fall

name: Avinash Prasad
review_text:
Dassam falls is one of the most beautiful tourist place in Jharkhand. This place is very popular amongst people who loves natural water falls and also for others. This place is 110 kms from Jamshedpur and 30 to 40 kms from Ranchi. You can reach almost near by 500 mtrs through the vehicles. Parking lot is easily available everywhere for all type of vehicles including long busses. Foods are also available at this place at a slightly high price because the place is almost 12 kms away from the main highway. Safe view points have been created by the government where you can enjoy the water falls view safely and also take selfies without worry. One reach near the water fall by using foot steps from the view point.
This place is only for one day visit because no resort or rest house is available for stay at night. Entry fee for parking is 30 rs (As on Dec19).
The water fall from the hight of 144 feet. Please post your query if you need the answer.

Ranchi city is the capital of Jharkhand state. This city is very important in terms of tradition and historical value.
Ranchi has the power to absorb the crowd, even if it is not flashy. And the natural beauty is amazing. You can visit the city of Ranchi near Kolkata this winter. Apart from various beauties, you must see the tenth waterfall. Ten streams descend here. There are many hidden shops nearby. Enjoy tea singara and special pakoras while watching the tenth waterfall.

There are few things which I was not happy about.
Firstly the road- Road needs renovation.
Signage - Road side signage is not proper, there is one place where it shows that Dassam falls is in right and on the same place its written that Dassam falls is on left, so its really confusing.
Food- I know near the tourist destination rate of the foods are high. But there foods rates are really so high and the quality also is not good. If you are spending money on food then you need atleast tasty and hygienic food. Its not there. So, my suggestion if you are bringing your own food thats better.

Rest all are fine. Local people helps others and they are working as a lifeguards as well.

name: siva prasad
review_text: Approximately 42 kms from ranchi it is an amazing waterfall that i have seen till date. Public transport does not go here so you will have to arrange a private vehicle to visit Dassam Falls. Although the place is a bit badly reputated because of its past experiences it seemed much more developed from what i heard from my freinds belonging to ranchi. So i though of not taking any risk and planned my journey in such a way that i reach there by mid noon. It is located around 7 -8kms inside from the ranchi - jamshedpur highway. That 7 kms stretch is not much developed. Narrow roads seeming like that you are travellling in jungle made me a bit tense, but being a sunday there is much floating traffic. But i ll suggest anyone to plan their journey between 11 to 4 such that you will get back to the highway before sunset. The waterfalls is definitely a stunning place especially during October and November with huge quantities of water and a must visit place to visit near ranchi.

name: Saubhik Das
review_text:
Wonderful, breathtaking; an experience beyond my expectations. Words just simply fall short. You have to be there to relish the majestic, picturesque wonder of our nature. One weekend with family to cherish.
Went by our car; exit from Ranchi was really a headache due to grotesque, carefully mismanaged traffic. But once you cross the limits of city, rest of the journey is enjoyable amid the tranquil nature; except for couple of areas due to construction work for widening of the road. The road condition undoubtedly be better once the work concludes. After you reach the destination, the view and formidable sound of water falling from 144 ft will surely blow your mind. Highly recommended to visit during monsoons; in winter or summer, i guess the view might not be that much overwhelming.
Cleanliness has been maintained compared to other places ( patratu valley, Jonha fall) may be because uncivilized, habitual litter mongering tourists are not that familiar with that place.
You could have tea/ snacks at local food stalls there; could carry your own food also.
Local people are good and courteous.
Better you finish off by 5pm and start your back journey.
Highly recommended to visit the place; it feels one could spend the whole day savouring the nature.

name: sur sangam world
review_text: Dassam Falls, the name has been derived from the number of the streams that fall from a distance of 144 feet above, from the River Kanchi. Dassam falls is also known as Dassam Ghagh. This is amongst one of the other beautiful waterfalls of the region for which tourists come from everywhere and it has greenery all around. It's musical and empowering, the tunes and melody that you encounter, is a different feeling in all. It is not recommended to play and/or bath in, as it is very dangerous, especially for kids. If you are interested in recreational activities, there are facilities provided on the Kanchi River. It's located on the Ranchi- Tata road which is approximately 34 kms from Ranchi.

name: Divyaang Tiwary
review_text: A real good place for a get away into the lap of nature. Though not for the lazy ones because you need to climb down 218 stairs and then the same number up as well. Its around 10kms interior from the main national highway and no good hotel or restaurant is anyway near. Also, even though the roads are good, you might run into a few patches of bad road in the 10km interior section and mind you, finding a puncture repairing shop in there is not easy. Also kindly drive really slow in the village areas cause even if you accidentally run over a chicken (they always tend to run into vehicles), you are in for some serious trouble. The water falls from a height of around 144ft and i will recommend going there during the rainy season cause that is when you can see the waterfall in its peak. Also, dont try to get too close to the water cause it is real deep and forms a kind of current underwater that tends to pull you right inside it, ultimately drowning you. And the rocks too are kind of slippery so be careful around them in the persuit to get that perfect picture. Kudos!

name: anand gothi
review_text:
Ranchi has some wonderful waterfalls of which Dasam is my personal favourite. From a trickle in summers to thunderous in monsoon and gentle in winters, it is always a treat. Have frequenting this since I was a child. Dasam falls infrastructure has changed a lot over the last couple of decades, thanks to the state tourism department and is more accessible. Swimming in the falls is dangerous and every year a couple of lives are lost, so enter the water at your own risk.
Overall a natural visual delight..

name: RicK 47
review_text:
Location - 23deg08'36''N85deg27'59''E .
Dassam is a changed form of word Da:song which means in mundari language the act of pouring water. Da: means water and song means pouring or measuring. The water fall resembles like somebody is pouring water so the name was Da:song earlier but afterwards the name was changed to Dassam.
Dassam Falls is a natural cascade across the Kanchi River, a tributary of the Subarnarekha River. The water falls from a height of 44 metres (144 ft).

review_text: Beautiful fall at Jharkhand. Very popular waterfall. It turns very much beautiful in the rainy season. A popular picnic spot for school students . A small children park for fun and entertainment . Naturally beautiful . A popular film shoot place also. The roads connected to the waterfall is in good condition. Toilet and urinals are available on both side of the waterfall.But you have to bathe in the river water which is also very enjoyable. Parking for bus, bike and private cars are available. The beautiful and also a dangerous place for selfie Lovers. A must visit place for nature Lovers.

name: Suvajit Mishra
review_text: A tourist spot. One of the most popular water falls in jharkhand & all over India. So many tourists visit every day in picnic season. Great view & atmosphere. There is high rock both side of the falls. And there is watch point for people to saw the water flow. Hill tracking adventure can be experienced little bit which is enjoyable. Lots of parking lot & stall /shop available. Drinking water, Toilet & bathrooms service available which is driven by the Govt. Mainly During the winter, lots of crowd gathered. People came from all over the place during the picnic season & local people regularly visits there. There are many spot for picnic. Very good destination for group, school, college tour. Overall must visit destination for travel lovers & tourists.
